## Epic 3: The Chat API

**Capability:** End-to-end chat pipeline with SSE streaming — user sends text, gets a streamed AI response
**Layers:** L2, L3, L6, L10

**Concepts to Master (Epic-level):**
- Exception hierarchies in Java — checked vs unchecked, when to extend RuntimeException, how `@ControllerAdvice` maps exceptions to HTTP status codes
- DTO pattern — why entities must never leak past the service layer, what happens if they do (lazy loading exceptions, circular references, data exposure)
- Server-Sent Events (SSE) — how SSE differs from WebSocket (unidirectional vs bidirectional), how `Flux<ServerSentEvent>` works in Spring WebFlux, how the browser reads an SSE stream
- Strategy Pattern — why an interface + multiple implementations is better than if-else chains, how Spring's dependency injection auto-discovers all implementations
- Template Method Pattern — what the base class defines vs what subclasses override, when this is better than Strategy
- AOP (Aspect-Oriented Programming) — how Spring proxies work, what `@Around` advice does, why `@Audited` is cross-cutting
- Spring Profiles — how `application-{profile}.yml` overrides `application.yml`, how to activate profiles
- `@ConfigurationProperties` — type-safe config binding, validation with `@Validated`

